===Etymology===
Compare {{inh|zh|sit-pro|*tsuk ⪤ *tsik||to build}} (STEDT). Cognate with {{cog|bo|རྫོང||castle; fortress}}, {{cog|my|ဆောင်||room; chamber; hall}} ({{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}).
; ''an administrative division in historical Tibet or present-day Bhutan''
: {{bor+|zh|bo|རྫོང||district; province}}, and thus distantly cognate with the native senses including "ancestral temple" and revere".

